css:
@-moz-document url-prefix("https://workflowy.com") {
/* WorkFlowy 360px Wide Page for 1920x1080 Screen Resolution (FHD) (1080p)

The screenshot gives an example of this theme applied to two different browsers, each at different widths and with a different WorkFlowy userstyle applied (you can see/try/get these and other userstyles at my profile page).

I find it a useful size for using with the Windows Power Toys utility known as FancyZones that, for free, splits windows into multiple zones quickly and efficiently. I especially use this userstyle with WorkFlowy for a 524px x 1080px zone, but also wider or even a bit narrower. This is best done using a browser like the Microsoft Edge browser, since some browsers limit too much how narrow you can make them.

This also adds styling to the border corners so it loosely mimics a 3-inch by 5-inch "Rite in the Rain" brand waterproof pocket notebook.

Finally, this adds some font selections and styling. Comment those out if you wish. */
#page container,
.mainTreeRoot.selected {
    bottom: 12px;
}

.page {
    max-width: 360px;
    padding-left: 46px;
    padding-right: 42px;
    position: relative;
    top: 5px;
    border-width: 1px;
    border-style: solid;
    border-color: #95989A;
    -moz-border-radius: 1px 1px 49px 49px !important;
    border-radius: 1px 1px 49px 49px !important;
    padding-top: 15px;
    padding-bottom: 1px;
    margin-bottom: 56px;
    overflow-x: hidden;
}

.content {
    font-family: Arial, Helvetica, 'Sans-Serif';
    font-size: 1em;
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
    line-height: 1.306435em;
    /* 1.313em x 99.5% */
    position: relative;
}

.selected.project > .name > .content {
    font-size: 0.595em;
    letter-spacing: 0.00595em;
    line-height: 1.36315em;
    /*1.37em x 99.5% */
    position: relative;
    top: 10px;
}

.noted > .notes > .content {
    font-size: 0.831em;
    letter-spacing: 0.00831em;
    line-height: 1.279em;
    color: #8b8680;
}
}
